<p>Let''s say: apply all the recommendations from the practice lesson! Try to take more photos! The practice improves the information, and your photos will become more professional.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2>Straight or curved lines</h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Lines guide you from one point to another within the frame. Observe them and involve them in working with the object. Remember that lines can be straight or curved.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:image {"align":"center","id":101,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->
<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img src="https://beta.svanty.com/public/uploads/blog/2021/08/boat-3062045_1280-1024x682.jpg" alt="boat" class="wp-image-101"/></figure></div>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The boat deck creates the lines, which lead from the edge of the frame to the center. The viewer''s eyes will trace the line of the boat from land to water.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Converging lines are an effective technique that guides the eye from the foreground to the horizon. It is a very dynamic composition. Diagonal lines give a sense of movement, help to make a photo that affects the viewer.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Mastering the art of composition in photography','','inherit','closed','closed','','96-revision-v1','','','2021-08-16 07:20:51','2021-08-16 07:20:51','',96,'https://svanty.com/blog/?p=106',0,'revision','',0,'','en');
